Four passengers have been confirmed dead in an accident that occured on Wednesday morning in Erin-Oke, Osun State. According to eyewitness account, the road traffic crash occured on the Erin-Oke axis of the Ilesa-Akure expressway when a truck and Sienna bus collided. The eyewitness revealed that two adult males, an adult female and an infant died instantly as a result of the collision. As at the time of filing this report, the injured have been conveyed to Wesley Guild Hospital, Ilesa, for treatment while the corpses have been deposited at the morgue. Also, the Osun Sector Command of the Federal Road Safety Commission (FRSC) is yet to react to the development.